    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've built after thoroughly studying IRC, Nostr, Telegram, and the core SDK:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: 7 New Files in `extensions/pulseboard/`\n\n### What gets created\n\n| File | Key details |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `\"type\": \"module\"`, `openclaw` block with all 5 required channel fields |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, `channels: [\"pulseboard\"]`, minimal empty `configSchema` |\n| `src/types.ts` | 3 interfaces: `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime` + `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with all required adapters (config/setup/gateway/messaging stubs + outbound with `deliveryMode: \"direct\"`, `textChunkLimit: 4000`) |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry(…)` with `plugin as ChannelPlugin` cast + named re-exports |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` one-liner |\n\n### Critical patterns confirmed from existing plugins\n1. **`.js` on all relative imports** (ESM requirement)\n2. **`as ChannelPlugin` cast** in `index.ts` — matches IRC + Telegram exactly\n3. `getChatChannelMeta` needs a type cast for unregistered channel ids, then spread with overrides\n4. Runtime store imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` directly (Telegram pattern)\n5. `deliveryMode: \"direct\" as const` to prevent type widening\n\n### Verification after implementation\n- `pnpm tsgo` / `pnpm build` for type-check\n- `pnpm check` for lint\n- `git status` confirms zero modifications to existing files",
